Telecom Churn Reduction Recommendations

1. Improve Contract Retention
   - Provide incentives for customers on month-to-month plans to shift to annual contracts.
   - Introduce loyalty rewards for longer-tenure customers.

2. Reduce Service-Related Churn
   - Promote Online Security and Tech Support add-ons to high-risk segments.
   - Improve the onboarding experience for new fiber optic users.

3. Address Billing & Payment Friction
   - Encourage autopay enrollment through discounts.
   - Reduce churn among electronic check users with targeted communication.

4. Target High-Risk Segments
   - Segment: Month-to-month + Fiber optic + No online security.
   - Launch personalized retention campaigns with offers, bundles, or discounts.

5. Improve Customer Lifetime Value
   - Provide retention offers during 0–12 month period.
   - Increase service satisfaction early in the customer lifecycle.

These actions can reduce churn by 10–20 percent over time.
